<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ery &s;tones,"</Q> this remark how|ever, is probably rather good <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">han new;&mdash;but we were now arrived at Bettus, and the Guide pointed to the hou&s;e, where I was to get lodging and entertain|ment;&mdash;the violent &s;tench did not prevent my looking in,&mdash;the <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">avages &s;at lapping their oatmeal <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">nd milk, and the &s;wine were <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ttendant at the table. In &s;uch <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter"> &s;ituation, only one que&s;tion <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="pdcc" EXTENT="1 letter">ould properly be a&s;ked, which was, how many miles to Car|narvon?
